					<head>Mishnah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842" rend="visible">
						<summary>Sefer ha-ḥesheḳ by Joseph of Hamadan, a commentary on Pirḳe avot by Yosef ibn Shushan, Pereḳ mishnah by Shem Ṭov ibn Shem Ṭov, Nefesh he-ḥakhamah by Moses de Leon, and Perush masekhet Avot by Baḥya ben Asher.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="tmr-Hebr"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80017842">
							<locus from="1r" to="99r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-ḥesheḳ  </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר החשק</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88071000">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88071000" xml:lang="en">Joseph, de Hamadan, active 13th century-14th century (?)</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/88071000" xml:lang="he">יוסף משושן הבירה (?) </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Consists a kabbalistic exposition of the Tabernacle (openning verses of Exodus 25), the Song of Songs and the first chapter of Ezekiel.</p>
								<p>From folio 1r to 27r the language is Hebrew, the rest being Aramaic. </p>
								<p>Folios 1r-3r and 10r-12r are arranged peculiarly in two columns, the continuation of the left-hand column of folio 3r being the right-hand column of folio 1r, and from the right-hand column of folio 12r one has to turn to the right-hand column of folio 10r. Cf. the manner of writing of Mandaitic texts.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="v">
							<locus from="99r" to="190r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש פרקי אבות</title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">A commentary on Pirḳe avot</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/120148944">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/120148944" xml:lang="en">Ben Shushan, Yosef, active 14th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/120148944" xml:lang="he">בן שושן, יוסף </persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Fragments only.</p>
								<p>The author quotes Maimonides quite frequently, but also gives opinions from the standpoint of kabbalah.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="v">
							<locus from="190r" to="201r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרק משנה</title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Pereḳ mishnah</title>
							<note>
								<p>A fragment only. </p>
							</note>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/97282190">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/97282190" xml:lang="en">Ibn Shem Tov, Shem Tov ben Joseph ben Shem Tov, active 15th century</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/97282190" xml:lang="he">אבן שם טוב, שם טוב בן יוסף </persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="v">
							<title xml:lang="he">פירוש</title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush</title>
							<locus from="201r" to="217r"/>
							<note>
								<p>A kabbalistic commentary on various topics. Anonymous.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="v">
							<locus from="217r" to="286r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he">פירוש מסכת אבות</title>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Perush Masekhet avot</title>
							<author key="http://viaf.org/viaf/44658675">
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/44658675" xml:lang="en">Baḥya ben Asher ben Ḥlava, ?-1340</persName>
								<persName key="http://viaf.org/viaf/44658675" xml:lang="he">בחיי בן אשר אבן חלאוה </persName>
							</author>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">נשלם בעזרת ה' וישועתו זה הפירוש מפרקי אבות לרבי' בחיי בדיין <date calendar="Hebrew">יום שלישי י"ג לחדש אייר שנת ה'ר'צ'ד' ליצירה</date> והסימן דרכיו ראיתי ו'א'ר'פ'א'ה'ו' על ידי הצעיר הנאנח <name type="person" role="scribe">דוד חסון</name> והוא לחכם שלם ה"ר <name type="person" role="patron">שלמה הלוי בכ"ר החכם השלם ר' משה הלוי אלקאבץ</name> י'צ'ו'ב' השם יזכהו להגות בו וכו'. במתא <name type="place">סאלוניקי</name>:  <locus n="286r"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
